=== 0011_DTO038520_в”јОЈв•“в”ңв•“в•¬в””ПҶв•ЈВөв•ҳвүҘ.dita ===
Configuring Governance Rules   This system supports configuring data governance rules at the process level, project level, and sample level. Data governance rule-related configurations are initially completed by technical support. The initial configuration is used by default thereafter, and it can also be modified based on actual requirements. Process-level rules apply to all samples analyzed using the analysis process. Project-level rules apply to all samples within a project. Sample-level rules apply to specified samples within a project.

=== 0016_DTO037299_в”јОЈв•“в”ңв•ҘВ¬в•ҹвүӨ.dita ===
Configuration Requirements   The hardware configuration and software environment requirements for the OmicsNest series bioinformatics analysis platform are shown in the following table:            Hardware Configuration       Server     OmicsNest Bioinformatics Analysis Platform Standard Edition     OmicsNest Bioinformatics Analysis Platform Basic Edition     OmicsNest Bioinformatics Analysis Platform Professional Edition      Catalog No.      900-001186-00      900-001187-00      900-001285-00      CPU Intel Xeon Gold 6430 Г— 2 Intel Xeon 4514Y Г— 2    Intel Xeon Gold 6430 Г— 2      Memory   256 GB 128 GB    256 GB      SSD   2.5 TB 1.5 TB    2.5 TB      HDD   40 TB (Actual capacity approximately 28 TB after configuring RAID 5) 12 TB (Actual capacity approximately 7.3 TB after configuring RAID 5)    40 TB (Actual capacity approximately 28 TB after configuring RAID 5)     Monitor    23.8 inches     Software Environment Requirements      Operating System      Ubuntu 22.04 LTS or later      Browser      Chrome browser version 101 or later is recommended Using a browser version lower than recommended or a non-Chrome browser may cause some interfaces to display incorrectly.      Others      Spreadsheet editing software must be installed, such as LibreOffice      Compatible Sequencing Platforms      MGISEQ-200RS, MGISEQ-2000RS, DNBSEQ-G99RS, DNBSEQ-G99ARS, etc.      Compatible Laboratory Management Systems      ZLIMS      ZLIMS Lite V3.0.4 or later      PaaZ      V4.0.2 or later

=== 0007_DTO038517_в”јОЈв•“в”ңв•ӨвҲҷв–’в•ӣв•қв•ўв•“в•¬в””ПҶв•ЈВөв•ҳвүҘ.dita ===
Configuring Sample-Level Governance Rules   The operation steps are as follows: Click Data in the top navigation bar, and click Data Governance in the left navigation bar to enter the Data Governance interface. Enter query conditions in the query condition area. For example, select the analysis process PFI_v5_3 in the Analysis Process box, and click to find the target analysis process. Click in the Sample column of the Operation column to open the Sample Governance window. Click Add Governance Configuration, and perform the following operations based on actual requirements to configure various information: Perform the following operation steps to specify the samples requiring data governance: Click Sample ID to open the sample selection window. Check the target samples. If there are many samples in the list, you can set query conditions in the query condition area to filter. Click Submit to return to the Sample Governance window. Check the files that need governance on the right. Select the file type in the File Type field. Select the operation type in the Operation Type field. Delete: Moves data to the trash, which will be automatically deleted after 7 days. Physical Deletion: Directly deletes the file and cannot be recovered. Select Analysis Result in the Operation Object field. In the Execution Time field, select the start time and end time. (Optional) If you need to configure multiple governance rules, click Add Governance Configuration multiple times and perform step 4; or click Copy below this button to copy the configured rule and modify it as needed to quickly configure more rules. Click Submit. In the pop-up rule confirmation window, click Submit after confirming it is correct. The sample-level governance rule has been configured. The system will automatically execute this rule to govern data. Once data is deleted, it cannot be recovered. Please operate with caution. Before configuring governance rules, it is recommended to consult technical support.

=== 0017_DTO037291_в•қвүҘв•ңОҳ.dita ===
Introduction   The OmicsNest series bioinformatics analysis platforms include OmicsNest Bioinformatics Analysis Platform Standard Edition, OmicsNest Bioinformatics Analysis Platform Basic Edition, and OmicsNest Bioinformatics Analysis Platform Professional Edition. They integrate hardware systems and analysis software to achieve parallel task processing, simplifying the analysis process of high-throughput sequencing data, thereby shortening the data processing cycle. The hardware system of this device utilizes HP Z8 workstation servers, including network, computing, and storage resources. The analysis software is responsible for executing data processing and analysis in the background, interfacing with the MGI Standard Laboratory Management System (hereinafter referred to as ZLIMS Lite or this system). The overall process is summarized as follows: Issue analysis tasks through the graphical user interface of ZLIMS Lite, wait for the analysis software to complete data processing and analysis, and then view the analysis results and reports through ZLIMS Lite. The operation is simple and convenient, realizing full life cycle management from sample input to analysis report output. This product is for scientific research use only and cannot be used for clinical diagnosis.

=== 0021_DTO038529_в”јОЈв•қв– в–‘в–“в•ҡВҪ.dita ===
Accessory Safety   This instrument is a dedicated server. Do not install third-party software without authorization. If you need to install any third-party software, please confirm with technical support in advance.

=== 0009_DTO038518_в”јОЈв•“в”ңв”ҙвүҲв”Ӯв• в•қв•ўв•“в•¬в””ПҶв•ЈВөв•ҳвүҘ.dita ===
Configuring Process-Level Governance Rules   The operation steps are as follows: Click Data in the top navigation bar, and click Rule Management in the left navigation bar to enter the Rule Management interface. Enter the rule name or select an analysis process such as PFI_v5_3 in the query condition area, and click to find all rules created for this analysis process. Click in the Operation column of the target rule to enter the Edit Governance interface. Edit Governance Interface Click Add Governance Configuration, and perform the following operations based on actual requirements to configure various information: Check the files that need governance on the right. Select the file type in the File Type field. Select the operation type in the Operation Type field. Delete: Moves data to the trash, which will be automatically deleted after 7 days. Physical Deletion: Directly deletes the file and cannot be recovered. Select Analysis Result in the Operation Object field. Analysis Result: Represents the storage containing analysis result data. After selecting Analysis Result, the interface will display two fields: Force Execution and Remaining Space вүӨ. Select On for the Force Execution field to indicate that this governance rule will be forcibly executed. A value must be set in the Remaining Space вүӨ field, indicating that when the remaining storage is below this value, the system will forcibly execute this governance rule. Select Off for the Force Execution field to indicate that this governance rule will not be forcibly executed. Enter a numerical value in the Operation Cycle field, and select a unit from the list on the right, such as Year, Month, Day, etc. Select the time type in the Time Type field. Multiple selections are supported. If multiple options are selected, all selected time types must be met. Storage Time: Represents the time when data storage is completed. Delivery Time: Represents the time when data delivery is completed. Analysis Time: Represents the time when data analysis is completed. In the QC Result field, select Pass or Fail. Both can be selected simultaneously, or neither. The system will govern the eligible data based on the set configuration information. (Optional) If you need to configure multiple governance rules, click Add Governance Configuration multiple times and perform step 4; or click Copy below this button to copy the configured rule and modify it as needed to quickly configure more rules. Click Submit. In the pop-up rule confirmation window, click Submit after confirming it is correct. Upon completion, when analyzing samples using this analysis process, the system automatically applies this process-level rule to the corresponding project. Project-level rules can be adjusted later as needed. Once data is deleted, it cannot be recovered. Please operate with caution. Before configuring governance rules, it is recommended to consult technical support.

