=== 0020_DTO038524_в”ӮГӯв•Ўв•Әв•ҘВ¬в•ҹвүӨ.dita ===
Site Requirements   The placement environment for this instrument should refer to the cleanliness requirements of ISO 14644-1 Class 8.

=== 0010_DTO038521_в•Ёв”¬в•ҳГ·в•“в•¬в””ПҶв•ЈВөв•ҳвүҘ.dita ===
Adding Governance Rules   Default governance rules have already been configured in this system for the installed analysis software applications. To add new governance rules, perform the following operation steps: Click Data in the top navigation bar, and click Rule Management in the left navigation bar to enter the Rule Management interface. Rule Management Interface This interface displays all configured governance rules. Click Add Rule in the upper right corner to enter the Add Rule interface. Fill in the rule name, etc., select the analysis process, and click Submit. Upon completion, the system returns to the Rule Management interface, and the newly added governance rule is automatically displayed in the list below, with the status Enabled by default. (Optional) To disable a governance rule, click in the Operation column, then click Confirm in the pop-up dialog box.

=== 0012_DTO038532_в••в”јв•©Г·.dita ===
Overview   Data governance refers to the periodic processing of data stored on this device, such as physical deletion. Data governance rules can be configured through ZLIMS Lite based on actual business usage requirements. After configuring the rules, this device will automatically execute the rules to complete data governance. During the governance process, the status and progress can be viewed through ZLIMS Lite.

=== 0014_DTO038523_PFIв•ҡПҶв•қв– в••в”јв•©Г·.dita ===
PFI Software Overview   PFI software is a companion data processing software designed for high-throughput sequencing data from various MGIEasy metagenomic/metatranscriptomic kits. This software includes modules for data filtering, microbial identification, antibiotic resistance gene annotation, virulence factor annotation, and report generation. This software is suitable for processing high-throughput sequencing data from the following metagenomic/metatranscriptomic kits:        Type      Kit Name      Metagenomics      MGIEasy Fast Enzyme Digestion Library Prep Set      MGIEasy Fast PCR-FREE Enzyme Digestion Library Prep Set      MGIEasy Cell-free DNA Library Prep Set      Metatranscriptomics      MGIEasy rRNA Depletion Kit      MGIEasy Fast RNA Library Prep Set

=== 0023_DTO038533_в•ЎП„в•һВ°в–‘в–“в•ҡВҪ.dita ===
Electrical Safety   Ensure the instrument is correctly grounded and the grounding resistance meets the requirements. Otherwise, it may cause leakage or even electric shock hazards. Do not remove the instrument casing, exposing internal components. Otherwise, it may cause electric shock hazards. Do not use this instrument near strong radiation sources (such as unshielded RF sources). Otherwise, it may reduce instrument accuracy. Before using the instrument for the first time, it is recommended to evaluate the electromagnetic environment. Ensure the input voltage meets the instrument requirements. Before using the instrument, ensure the voltage at the laboratory power outlet or UPS output (if any) is within the required range. Otherwise, it may reduce the performance of the instrument's electronic components.

=== 0019_DTO038525_в–’О©в•ҹвҢҗ.dita ===
