=== 0022_DTO038527_в•—В·в•Ёв•Ўв–‘в–“в•ҡВҪ.dita ===
Mechanical Safety   Ensure the instrument is placed on a stable, level surface that meets the load-bearing requirements and is not easily moved. Otherwise, it may cause personal injury.

=== 0008_DTO038519_в”јОЈв•“в”ңв•§Оөв”Җв”җв•қв•ўв•“в•¬в””ПҶв•ЈВөв•ҳвүҘ.dita ===
Configuring Project-Level Governance Rules   Projects corresponding to an analysis process automatically apply the configured process-level governance rules. If necessary, project-level governance rules can be adjusted for the project. The operation steps are as follows: Click Data in the top navigation bar, and click Data Governance in the left navigation bar to enter the Data Governance interface. Data Governance Interface Enter query conditions in the query condition area. For example, select the analysis process PFI_v5_3 in the Analysis Process box, and click to find the target analysis process. Click in the Project column of the Operation column to open the Governance Rules window. Click Add Governance Configuration, and configure various information based on actual requirements. For specific configuration information, refer to Step 4. Click Submit. In the pop-up rule confirmation window, click Submit after confirming it is correct. Upon completion, the system will automatically execute this project-level governance rule to govern data. Once data is deleted, it cannot be recovered. Please operate with caution. Before configuring governance rules, it is recommended to consult technical support.

